.TH "xilinx_dpdma_handle_err_irq" 9 "xilinx_dpdma_handle_err_irq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xilinx_dpdma_handle_err_irq \- Handle DPDMA error interrupt
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xilinx_dpdma_handle_err_irq
.BI "(struct xilinx_dpdma_device *xdev "  ","
.BI "u32 isr "  ","
.BI "u32 eisr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xdev" 12
DPDMA device
.IP "isr" 12
masked Interrupt Status Register
.IP "eisr" 12
Error Interrupt Status Register
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Handle if any error occurs based on \fIisr\fP and \fIeisr\fP. This function disables
corresponding error interrupts, and those should be re-enabled once handling
is done.
